Quiz: making an sf object

viewof q1 = Inputs.radio(
  ["st_read()", "st_as_sf()", "st_transform()", "st_crs()"],
  { label: "Which function converts a data frame with lon/lat columns into an sf object?" }
);
html`${q1 == null ? "" : q1 === "st_as_sf()" ? "&lt;strong&gt;Correct.&lt;/strong&gt; st_as_sf() turns a data frame with coordinate columns into an sf object." : "&lt;em&gt;Not quite.&lt;/em&gt; Which function turns lon/lat columns into geometry?"}`

Quiz: what is EPSG:4326?

viewof q2 = Inputs.radio(
  ["Geodetic, in degrees", "Projected, in metres", "Always a UTM zone", "An equal-area projection"],
  { label: "EPSG:4326 (WGS 84) is..." }
);
html`${q2 == null ? "" : q2 === "Geodetic, in degrees" ? "&lt;strong&gt;Correct.&lt;/strong&gt; EPSG:4326 (WGS 84) is geodetic: longitude/latitude in degrees." : "&lt;em&gt;Try again.&lt;/em&gt; 4326 is the familiar lon/lat system."}`

